citances.sentence: I note also that in Gant v Commissioner Australian Federal Police (No 2) [2006] FCA 1494 Collier J cited Meredith as authority for the proposition that an order upholding an objection to competency, on the basis that a decision is not reviewable under the ADJR Act, is an interlocutory decision, although her Honour in that case seemed to have no hesitation in granting leave to appeal.
